When we entered the cafe, we were not greeted and it immediately had a poor atmosphere. It smelled really bad when we walked in and it seemed dingy. The man that was making the food was very negative and had a lot of gross food practices. He kept touching his face and walking around the cafe grabbing stuff; he never once changed his gloves. We spent fifty dollars for three drinks and three sandwiches that took almost thirty minutes to arrive. The patio area was disgusting and only had four chairs for seven tables; one chair was broken. My iced mocha that I ordered didn’t even have sweetener and was bitter. All of our drinks were made poorly and the food could of easily be made at home. I would not recommend this place!

I hate to see this not rated higher. I visit this location frequently and have always been satisfied. I read the reviews and for the most part the bad reviews happen to be from the customer's ignorance. I like how the owner responds to reviews. It's seems if people just communicated better with the staff they would enjoy their experiences a lot better. That being said the Cuban is authentic, it is not a Cuban coffee house, and lastly it's a little more pricey because it's fresh and made to order.  It's not a multi million dollar chain it's a small, honest, local business.  I personally don't mind paying a little more for quality.
